main event: A military observer at Keesler AFB in Mississippi spotted an elongated fireball with an orange-yellowish flame and falling pieces on March 29, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 1.5 to 2 minutes.
The object was described as a 4-engine airliner-sized elongated fireball with an orange-yellowish flame.
The object was traveling in a westerly direction and appeared to be straight and level.
The observer was standing in a neighbor's yard and looked up to see the object overhead.
No other events were correlated with this single report, and it was most likely a re-entry burnout of some space debris.
sighted object: elongated fireball with orange-yellowish flame and falling pieces
